# Summarize This Folder
# AI reads an entire folder of docs and produces a one-page executive summary.

[var: SITE = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]
[var: LIBRARY = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/Q4%20Planning/Strategy%20Docs/]

[section: setup]

Verify the "Q4 Planning" library exists with a "Strategy Docs" folder
containing four files: market-analysis.docx, product-priorities.docx,
sales-forecast.xlsx, budget-request.docx. This demo is read-only.

[navigate: ${LIBRARY}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

Confirm all four strategy documents are visible inside the folder.

[pause]

[section: demo]

[navigate: ${LIBRARY}]

Your leadership team needs a Q4 summary. The information is spread across four
documents from four different teams — market analysis, product priorities, sales
forecast, and budget. Normally you'd spend an hour reading and synthesizing.

[pause]

[open-chat]

[prompt: Read all the documents in this folder and write a one-page executive summary covering market context, product plans, revenue targets, and budget. Keep it to 5 paragraphs.]

[wait]

Copilot wove all four sources into a coherent narrative. Notice it pulled the
18% market growth from the analysis, the three product priorities, the $12.5M
target from sales, and the $300K budget overage — all in one summary. Point out
how it reads like a human wrote it, not a cut-and-paste job.

[pause]

Now let's ask the question no single document can answer.

[prompt: What's the biggest risk you see across these documents?]

[wait]

This is where it gets interesting. Copilot connected the $1.8M renewal risk
from sales with the $300K budget overage — a potential $2.1M swing that no
single document mentions. It sees across the whole folder.

[pause]

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/05-summarize-folder-final.png]

[section: reset]

This demo is read-only. Just start a new chat.

[new-chat]
